Bloomberg's Alix Steel reports 
that  China ’s economic growth slowed in the first two months 
of the year, with both exports and domestic demand moderating 
faster than analysts had forecast, building the case for 
Premier  Wen Jiabao  to accelerate stimulus measures. The 
world’s second-largest economy had the biggest trade deficit 
last month in at least 22 years. She speaks on Bloomberg 
Television's "InBusiness With Margaret Brennan." (Source: 
